          <h2>hooligan</h2>
          <p>A football news aggregator for football fans, by a football fan. <span style="font-size: 0.8em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.4); display: block; text-align: justify;">This application was my second project for General Assembly.  I built it using Rails 4, MongoDB, with Nokogiri and Mechanize for webscraping and soon with the Aylien Text Analysis API for text summarization. I chose to use web scraping after I realized that no API had the particular spectrum of information that I wanted.  I used RSpec, Factory Girl, and CircleCI for integrated testing.  The user can view a selection of football articles, write comments, and read other user's content in real time.  This project was inspired by my experiences in Barcelona, gradually becoming a football fan in the long, leisurely hours spent watching the sport and discussing research projects with my fellow students. It helped that the Faculty of Physical Chemistry, our home department, was located a stone's throw from Camp Nou.</span></p>
          <p><a class="btn btn-default" href="https://hooligans.herokuapp.com" role="button" target="_blank">View details &raquo;</a></p>
