          <h2>curator</h2>
          <p>A journaling site that uses natural language processing to curate art.<span style="font-size: 0.8em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.4); display: block; text-align: justify;">This was my fourth and final project for the WDI program.  I used Rails 4, MongoDB, RSpec, Factory Girl and CircleCI for testing.  I used the Skyttle Sentiment Analysis API to parse the text for keywords, and phrase and document level polarity analysis.  I saved the keywords and used a randomized subset as a search parameter for objects in the Rijksmuseum, the Brooklyn Museum, and the Cooper Hewitt Design Museum. The end goal is that the user can explore a selection of artwork curated by the keywords in the text they've written.  Currently, I am working on site security, and updating styling.  I am also adding the ability for users to save favorite images, and adding functionality to the keyword select feature on the post show pages.</span></p>
